1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:01,133
<i>You're just taking
advantage of the fact</i>

2
00:00:01,633 --> 00:00:02,300
<i> that her family kept us apart.</i>

3
00:00:02,967 --> 00:00:05,067
<i>I called you here
to tell you to your face,</i>

4
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:07,367
<i>that every time you force
yourself to talk to her,</i>

5
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:08,800
<i> Jade is the one who suffers.</i>

6
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:10,333
<i> If you really care about her,</i>

7
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:12,500
<i>you would think
about her situation.</i>

8
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:16,000
<i>He is alive.
That's Sandro Soliman.</i>

9
00:00:16,133 --> 00:00:18,033
<i>Leon and the others
need to know this.</i>

10
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:20,033
<i>You know, just answer it.
It might be important.</i>

11
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:21,367
<i>- Hello?
- Hello, Hell-- -</i>

12
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:22,467
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

13
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:23,700
<i> Hello?</i>

14
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:26,800
- [YELPS]
- [GRUNTS, BLADE SLICING FLESH]

15
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:28,667
<i>I kept my promise
to you guys, alright?</i>

16
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>De La Paz? If there's a cop
involved in Juan's case,</i>

17
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,000
<i>it means that Leon is
not safe inside.</i>

18
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:35,867
<i>If there's an accomplice, we
need an ally on our side, too.</i>

19
00:00:36,033 --> 00:00:38,167
<i>Do you think
Sir Andy and De La Paz</i>

20
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:39,767
<i>work together
on what happened to Juan?</i>

21
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,900
<i> Everyone believes so.</i>

22
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:46,500
[ENGINE STOPS,
HANDBRAKE ENGAGES]

23
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:50,200
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

24
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:52,800
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

25
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:59,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:13,067
What do you need to show me

27
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:15,033
that can't be shown
at the station?

28
00:01:16,767 --> 00:01:18,467
Go ahead, Martin, show him.

29
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:25,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

30
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:31,467
[GIO] I know the face of the guy
who interrogated me,

31
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,833
so you know your partner's
face even better.

32
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:39,067
You can't deny
that's De La Paz.

33
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:44,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

34
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:53,367
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:47,267
Where is this?

36
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:51,133
At the place where our siblings
believe Juan was locked up.

37
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:55,833
But what is De La Paz
doing here?

38
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,433
That's our question, too.

39
00:02:57,567 --> 00:03:00,400
What is he doing with
Juan's kidnappers?

40
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,900
[KIKO] One of those men there
is Juan's kidnapper.

41
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:07,800
Cheska and the others saw
his face themselves.

42
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:10,100
And sir, there's money.

43
00:03:10,233 --> 00:03:12,700
De La Paz is paying
those guys off.

44
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:19,033
Let's say De La Paz
is a corrupt cop,

45
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,567
but this still does not prove

46
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:24,733
that she is involved in the
kidnapping or Juan's death.

47
00:03:26,367 --> 00:03:29,100
This isn't enough evidence
for me to investigate him.

48
00:03:29,233 --> 00:03:32,433
But it is enough to doubt
the loyalty of that cop.

49
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:35,067
[KIKO] Sir.

50
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:39,300
You do believe us that De
La Paz can't be trusted, right?

51
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:45,300
Send me the video.

52
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:48,133
Along with the exact location
where it was shot.

53
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:50,767
[CLEARS THROAT]

54
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:52,867
[HENRI]
I can't promise anything,

55
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,067
but I'll see what I can do.

56
00:03:58,733 --> 00:04:00,133
Thank you, sir.

57
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,600
We didn't talk.

58
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,133
We didn't meet.

59
00:04:06,267 --> 00:04:11,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING,
THEN FADES]

60
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:13,500
Cheska, has your brother
replied to you yet?

61
00:04:13,633 --> 00:04:14,733
Not yet.

62
00:04:14,867 --> 00:04:15,867
- How about you?
- Me neither.

63
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

64
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:18,800
What could have happened there?

65
00:04:18,933 --> 00:04:21,833
Sir Henri is trustworthy, right?

66
00:04:21,967 --> 00:04:24,467
I hope so.
I hope he's not like Marina.

67
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,533
Don't ever do that again,
okay? It's not funny.

68
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,233
Hey, are you mad?

69
00:04:30,733 --> 00:04:33,733
I let you investigate before
because I was with you.

70
00:04:33,867 --> 00:04:35,900
But this thing with Marina?

71
00:04:36,033 --> 00:04:37,300
Isn't that a good thing?

72
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:40,067
We proved she's a bad cop.

73
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,133
But I'm worried about you.

74
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:44,900
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:46,333
So, you're not happy?

76
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:50,700
No.
It's not like that, okay?

77
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,367
The two of you...

78
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,100
You are the closest to me
here at the hotel,

79
00:04:54,233 --> 00:04:56,267
and I don't want anything
bad to happen to you.

80
00:04:57,833 --> 00:05:01,467
Fine. On our next adventure,
you're coming with us.

81
00:05:02,967 --> 00:05:05,667
Cheska, stop it with
the adventures.

82
00:05:06,933 --> 00:05:08,633
Oh come on, I'm just kidding.

83
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:13,500
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

84
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:14,667
But, thank you.

85
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,833
Really.

86
00:05:19,067 --> 00:05:20,633
It's a big deal.

87
00:05:23,767 --> 00:05:25,200
We're so good, right?

88
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,300
[CLICKS TONGUE]

89
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:35,433
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,700
Luna! Jade!

91
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:42,233
They're here.

92
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:46,200
Well?

93
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:48,267
What did he say?
What did Sir Henri say?

94
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,333
He said he'll see
what he can do.

95
00:05:50,467 --> 00:05:52,933
- That's it?
- It's still a good thing.

96
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,500
Any other cop would
have kicked us out.

97
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:57,933
So, what? We'll just wait
for what he finds out?

98
00:05:58,067 --> 00:05:59,000
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

99
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:00,867
We can't.

100
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,167
Why?

101
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:04,433
Why? Do you still suspect
Sir Henri?

102
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:06,533
It's not that.

103
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,833
I just can't sit around
and wait here.

104
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:11,367
So, what's your plan?

105
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:15,833
What if we tell Andy that we
have the clues to the treasure?

106
00:06:15,967 --> 00:06:17,133
What?

107
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:18,833
Are we giving it to him?

108
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:23,700
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:24,700
No.

110
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:27,467
We will just use the clues
as bait

111
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:30,300
to make Andy confess to
all the bad things he did.

112
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:35,500
To Leon. And to our dads.

113
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:37,700
Then we'll record
the confession.

114
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,800
That's what we need, right?

115
00:06:42,533 --> 00:06:46,733
Uncle Andy, confessing
to murder? No way.

116
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:48,867
Then, at least,
he'll lose his temper

117
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,533
and we will see it on him.

118
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:53,133
You're putting yourselves
in danger.

119
00:06:53,267 --> 00:06:54,933
[GIO] Jade.

120
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:56,900
We already talked about this,
right?

121
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:58,400
I thought we're all in?

122
00:06:58,533 --> 00:07:00,167
I get it.

123
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:03,033
I get it! But this early?

124
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:06,100
We are going to risk
our lives this early.

125
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:09,867
Yes, we might get Leon out.
But what about us?

126
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:16,800
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

127
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:22,933
Jade is right.
It's too early.

128
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,867
So, what?

129
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:29,200
We'll just wait?

130
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:31,333
We'll just wait for Sir Henri
to catch De La Paz

131
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:32,700
and make her confess?

132
00:07:33,667 --> 00:07:36,300
When will that be?
Tell me.

133
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:40,333
In a month? In a year?

134
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:42,500
When?

135
00:07:43,933 --> 00:07:46,200
Luna. Jade.

136
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,800
I'm with him this time.

137
00:07:48,967 --> 00:07:54,067
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,833
You don't like Gio's plan?

139
00:07:57,667 --> 00:07:59,367
So, what do you
think we should do?

140
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:05,733
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

141
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,833
We need to do this.

142
00:08:08,967 --> 00:08:10,167
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

143
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:13,467
Until Andy is locked up,
none of us are safe.

144
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,400
Even Leon inside prison.

145
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:19,633
And most importantly, I need
to keep repeating this to you,

146
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,167
this is for justice
for our fathers

147
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:24,267
who were killed without a fight

148
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:26,733
just because of that
damn treasure!

149
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:33,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

150
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,267
Luna.

151
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,000
Okay.

152
00:08:42,133 --> 00:08:43,633
I'll call Uncle Andy.

153
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:49,767
We can do this.

154
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:56,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

155
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,200
Edward.

156
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:15,767
Edward, please.

157
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:18,900
Please, for the last time,
I'm begging you.

158
00:09:19,033 --> 00:09:21,267
Don't talk to me anymore.
Don't come see me.

159
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,533
We can't meet anymore.

160
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:25,967
Jade, even until now, you
still haven't told me why?

161
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:28,467
The last time I was left
in the dark

162
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:30,400
was when you stood me up
at prom.

163
00:09:31,433 --> 00:09:33,733
After that, we stopped
being friends, Jade!

164
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:37,567
Jade, didn't I tell you?

165
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:42,333
If you told me your reason,
I would understand.

166
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:49,500
Jade, it hurts to be left
by someone important,

167
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:51,533
especially when
you don't understand why.

168
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:53,667
Edward, but this is
a different story.

169
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,633
This isn't just a simple case

170
00:09:55,767 --> 00:09:57,633
of ghosting you at prom.
This is a much bigger problem!

171
00:09:57,767 --> 00:10:00,967
But it feels the same, Jade!

172
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:04,400
You're disappearing again
without me knowing why.

173
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:15,633
That's why it's hard
to tell you because...

174
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:19,033
because it involves your dad.

175
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,833
That's clear to me, Jade.

176
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:26,933
It's clear how your siblings
push me away!

177
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:30,567
How Kiko and his brothers
look at me?

178
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:33,600
But why?!

179
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:36,333
What did Dad do?
So if I know, I can fix it

180
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,400
and you won't be mad at me!

181
00:10:38,533 --> 00:10:45,433
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

182
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:48,000
Yes, Jade. I love him.

183
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:49,600
I love my dad.

184
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:55,567
But I know right from wrong.

185
00:10:58,367 --> 00:11:01,467
I won't blindly follow him.

186
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,467
Jade, please.

187
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,033
Please, Jade.
Make me understand,

188
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:06,500
what is going on?

189
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:12,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

190
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:18,533
Uncle Andy's who we think
got Leon locked up.

191
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,567
That he put Juan's body
in the car.

192
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:29,667
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:11:35,433 --> 00:11:37,700
Is this all because
of the partnership?

194
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:39,967
Edward, he talked to Leon.

195
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,367
He blackmailed him

196
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:43,233
just to become our
business partner--

197
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:44,733
He's just there
for the opportunity--

198
00:11:44,867 --> 00:11:46,067
There!

199
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,567
That's exactly why I didn't
want to tell you.

200
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:49,933
Because at the end of the day,

201
00:11:50,067 --> 00:11:51,933
you'll still take
your father's side!

202
00:11:52,733 --> 00:11:54,667
But, Jade, that doesn't mean...

203
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,133
[SIGHS]

204
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:59,667
Edward, he has another
intention with the hotel.

205
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:02,933
He wants to get the
hidden treasure.

206
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:05,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

207
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:07,000
Jade, what are you
talking about?

208
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:09,133
Treasure?

209
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:11,900
Jade, are you serious?

210
00:12:13,533 --> 00:12:15,067
It's hard to believe.

211
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:21,933
But that's the only reason
he's interested in the hotel.

212
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:26,700
That's why we want to
find the treasure first,

213
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:28,500
before Uncle Andy does.

214
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,700
Are you planning something
against Dad?

215
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:33,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:12:33,967 --> 00:12:35,133
I already told you everything

217
00:12:35,267 --> 00:12:37,033
so you wouldn't be
left in the dark.

218
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:44,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

219
00:12:51,967 --> 00:12:53,133
[ANDY] Yes, Luna?

220
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:55,700
Dad.

221
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,000
No, no.
You don't have to apologize.

222
00:12:59,133 --> 00:13:00,400
You know we're in the
hotel business,

223
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:02,567
so it's normal that
we meet there.

224
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,233
Okay, I'll see you
tomorrow then.

225
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,033
Bye.

226
00:13:09,633 --> 00:13:10,500
Good news, bud.

227
00:13:10,633 --> 00:13:12,633
Our new business venture
is pushing through.

228
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:15,100
Luna wants to meet me
at the hotel tomorrow.

229
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,100
No.

230
00:13:17,867 --> 00:13:19,100
Don't go there.

231
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:22,833
Why?

232
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:25,100
Is there a problem
if I go to 88?

233
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:28,300
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:48,133
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:14:02,867 --> 00:14:09,700
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

236
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:19,700
If Juan was really hidden here,

237
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:23,000
<i>and De la Paz has a connection
to Juan's kidnappers...,</i>

238
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:26,267
<i>then she might really be an
accomplice, just like Gio said.</i>

239
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,533
Dad...

240
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:36,500
Let go of Hotel 88.

241
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:39,200
I'm begging you.

242
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:45,233
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:03,933
[CLEARS THROAT]

244
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:06,200
Where is Luna? She was
the one who called me.

245
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,400
They're busy.

246
00:15:07,533 --> 00:15:09,767
So we'll be the ones
to meet you instead.

247
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,767
Sit, please.

248
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:17,400
- Coffee? Whiskey?
- No, thanks.

249
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,167
What is this about?

250
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:22,267
It's about Leon's release.

251
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,133
We'll get straight to the point.

252
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:28,733
Leon told us you might be
able to help him get out.

253
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,767
Of course.

254
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:31,867
[GIO] How?

255
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,400
I know a judge.

256
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:38,367
And pay him?

257
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,867
We can do that too.
What else?

258
00:15:43,533 --> 00:15:45,333
The evidence is strong.

259
00:15:45,467 --> 00:15:47,867
Juan's body was found
in the back of his car.

260
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,267
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:54,200
I can have that evidence
dismissed.

262
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:56,767
You don't know me that well yet.

263
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:59,867
But I'll need something
in return.

264
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,233
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

265
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:06,333
We can't give you
the partnership.

266
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:08,400
Then we have nothing else
to talk about.

267
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,200
That's my only condition.

268
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:18,300
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:21,433
Gio, just tell him.

270
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:27,833
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

271
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:30,767
There is something
else we can offer you.

272
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,567
if you're interested.

273
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:34,233
[CLEARS THROAT]

274
00:16:37,233 --> 00:16:38,400
What is it?

275
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:40,633
Clues.

276
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:44,167
About the hidden treasure.

277
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:48,767
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:50,367
Clues?

279
00:16:52,867 --> 00:16:54,967
Our father left us a video
before he died.

280
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,933
<i> And I want you to know</i>

281
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:09,600
<i>that there's a hidden treasure
in this hotel.</i>

282
00:17:10,533 --> 00:17:15,000
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

283
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:18,333
After we watched it,
we searched.

284
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,200
We found clues in his room.

285
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:23,767
But we don't know
if it's real or not.

286
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:26,733
If it is real,

287
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:30,367
we can split it.

288
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:38,267
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

289
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:40,467
We can share everything
with you.

290
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,300
We also need the money.

291
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:43,667
Fifty-fifty.

292
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,700
And, uh...

293
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:53,400
How many of those clues
do you already have?

294
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:54,933
[MARTIN] Three.

295
00:17:57,167 --> 00:18:04,000
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:16,933
- [LAUGHING MANIACALLY]
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:20,000
What's so funny?

298
00:18:21,067 --> 00:18:22,633
You guys are hilarious.

299
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,567
Guys, it's 2026.

300
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:27,167
Do you still believe
that kind of stuff?

301
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:28,333
[KIKO] Papa left a video.

302
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:29,500
[ANDY] So what?

303
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:30,700
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:33,467
Boys, I'll be honest
with you, okay?

305
00:18:34,033 --> 00:18:35,300
Fred and your dad,

306
00:18:35,433 --> 00:18:36,667
they were weird.

307
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,100
I'm sorry,
but that's the truth.

308
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:42,333
They had been making up
stories for a long time.

309
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:45,333
Now...

310
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,533
I'm guessing there won't be
any deals today.

311
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:52,200
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

312
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,533
I'm just wasting my time here.

313
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:59,933
Now, if you make me a partner,
I will help Leon.

314
00:19:00,067 --> 00:19:01,133
It's that simple.

315
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,467
Good day, gentlemen.

316
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,133
[MUSIC FADING]

317
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:16,500
[WAVES LAPPING]

318
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:18,433
[HENRI] Excuse me. I'm sorry,
but you have to leave now.

319
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:20,000
- Come on.
- We hope you understand.

320
00:19:20,133 --> 00:19:23,100
[MARINA] The police will
handle this. Thank you.

321
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:30,067
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

322
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:48,200
[KIKO]
Andy didn't agree to our offer.

323
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:51,567
Does that mean he doesn't
know anything about money?

324
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:53,733
He knows.

325
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:57,800
I could see it in his actions,
in his eyes.

326
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:00,667
I can tell how my clients feel
when they're about to secure

327
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,167
the condo they've been eyeing.

328
00:20:02,567 --> 00:20:03,800
Andy was like that.

329
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:05,533
[MARTIN] Gio's right.

330
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,433
Andy had a different look
on his face

331
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:09,100
when we mentioned
the clues.

332
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,433
If so...

333
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:15,300
we need to take action.

334
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:17,633
We need to keep piecing
the clues together.

335
00:20:17,767 --> 00:20:18,933
Once the treasure is found,

336
00:20:19,067 --> 00:20:21,133
that bastard's true colors
will also be revealed.

337
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:24,133
[KIKO] But how can we
continue searching if...

338
00:20:24,267 --> 00:20:26,633
Andy already knows
the clues exist?

339
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:28,900
He's definitely going
to have us followed.

340
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:30,233
We have to be careful.

341
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,367
This is what Gio was
talking about,

342
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:34,533
that our lives will be
in danger.

343
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,567
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

344
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:37,667
[MARTIN] But we can't stop.

345
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,433
There are so many answers
that will be answered

346
00:20:39,567 --> 00:20:40,900
if we find the treasure.

347
00:20:41,933 --> 00:20:42,867
Okay.

348
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:45,700
I'll share the news with Luna
and the others.

349
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:48,000
Remember, as we search
for the treasure...

350
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,467
we must watch
each other's back.

351
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:53,467
We're the only ones
on the same side here.

352
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:57,767
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

353
00:20:57,900 --> 00:20:59,100
[DOOR OPENS]

354
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,133
[LEON] Sir Henri.

355
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:08,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

356
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:12,167
Who was your partner
in the murder of Juan Soliman?

357
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:13,900
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

358
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:19,333
You asked me that before,
and I already answered.

359
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,633
I know you had an accomplice.

360
00:21:22,133 --> 00:21:23,233
Who?

361
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:24,500
One of your siblings?

362
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:26,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

363
00:21:26,633 --> 00:21:28,267
[HENRI] One of Michael's sons?

364
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,100
Or did you ask for help
from one of the Hotel 88 staff?

365
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:34,467
Are you suspecting them?

366
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,333
If you don't say anything,

367
00:21:36,467 --> 00:21:38,367
I'll investigate them all.

368
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:40,467
Sooner or later,

369
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,500
I'll uncover who else is
connected to you and Juan.

370
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:46,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

371
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:47,300
What, Leon?

372
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,767
Are you finally going to speak?

373
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:55,367
Treasure?

374
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:56,600
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

375
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:58,900
Are you saying that was
Andy Arellano's motive?

376
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:00,400
[LEON] Yes.

377
00:22:01,167 --> 00:22:03,467
He had Juan kidnapped
so that he could force him

378
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:06,733
into revealing where
the treasure was hidden.

379
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:09,633
That's why he wants
to be a part of Hotel 88.

380
00:22:12,067 --> 00:22:13,100
[HENRI SNICKERS]

381
00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:14,167
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

382
00:22:14,300 --> 00:22:15,567
What's funny?

383
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:19,600
Who wouldn't laugh
at what you're saying?

384
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,633
"Treasure"?

385
00:22:22,467 --> 00:22:24,667
It sounds like you're
playing hide-and-seek!

386
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:27,133
I'm telling the truth.

387
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,233
You must really hate
the Arellanos

388
00:22:30,367 --> 00:22:32,100
to accuse him of that.

389
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:34,433
Andy isn't the only one.

390
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,933
I'm pretty sure he has an
accomplice with enough power

391
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:39,367
to get me to prison.

392
00:22:39,867 --> 00:22:41,067
An accomplice?

393
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

394
00:22:43,933 --> 00:22:44,933
[LEON] Yes.

395
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:49,567
Andy couldn't have set me up
without a connection.

396
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:52,467
He's clearly working
with someone in authority.

397
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:59,033
Are you really sure about that?

398
00:22:59,633 --> 00:23:01,233
We have evidence.

399
00:23:01,367 --> 00:23:03,100
Me and my siblings.

400
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:05,567
[HENRI] Just a moment ago,
it was a treasure.

401
00:23:05,700 --> 00:23:07,433
Now you're saying there's an
accomplice in the police force.

402
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:09,733
You'd better straighten out,
Almazan.

403
00:23:09,867 --> 00:23:12,633
You might just bury yourself
deeper in the case.

404
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:19,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

405
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:25,067
[DOOR CREAKING]

406
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:29,733
[DOOR OPENS]

407
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:32,067
[DOOR CLOSES]

408
00:23:35,667 --> 00:23:37,233
We have a new plan.

409
00:23:37,867 --> 00:23:39,600
We'll keep an eye
on Michael's children

410
00:23:39,733 --> 00:23:41,633
while they look
for the treasure.

411
00:23:42,733 --> 00:23:44,833
Why don't we take the clues
by force

412
00:23:44,967 --> 00:23:46,500
and look for the
treasure ourselves?

413
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,633
We can't just do that.

414
00:23:51,767 --> 00:23:54,467
They're more familiar with
Hotel 88 than we are.

415
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,200
It will be easier for us
in the long run

416
00:23:56,367 --> 00:23:58,267
if we just let them find it,

417
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:00,000
and then we'll step in
and take control.

418
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:02,700
Okay.

419
00:24:03,267 --> 00:24:04,900
I'll tell our people.

420
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,200
By the way...

421
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:11,533
Leon...

422
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:13,600
What about Leon?

423
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:15,433
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

424
00:24:15,567 --> 00:24:18,000
He told Syvera
about the treasure.

425
00:24:19,167 --> 00:24:22,533
And that you're the mastermind
behind Juan's murder.

426
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:26,800
What did Syvera say?

427
00:24:27,367 --> 00:24:28,800
He didn't believe any of it.

428
00:24:29,267 --> 00:24:30,433
He just laughed.

429
00:24:30,567 --> 00:24:31,900
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

430
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:35,367
But Leon said that he's sure
you have an accomplice

431
00:24:35,500 --> 00:24:36,967
among the authorities.

432
00:24:39,967 --> 00:24:41,967
Does he know anything
about our connection?

433
00:24:43,067 --> 00:24:44,033
[MARINA HUFFS]

434
00:24:44,167 --> 00:24:45,433
Damn you, Leon.

435
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:47,333
I could end up in trouble.

436
00:24:47,467 --> 00:24:49,167
[SIGHING]

437
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:52,733
I'll deal with him before
he can say anything more.

438
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:59,467
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

439
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,600
[MUSIC FADING]

440
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:03,100
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

441
00:25:03,267 --> 00:25:05,500
Be careful, Luna.

442
00:25:05,633 --> 00:25:07,867
I hope you have the right
coordinates this time.

443
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,933
You and Martin should
stay alert too, please.

444
00:25:10,067 --> 00:25:11,067
[PHONE CHIMING]

445
00:25:13,267 --> 00:25:14,600
Work stuff? Seriously?

446
00:25:15,133 --> 00:25:16,600
It's from Sari.

447
00:25:16,733 --> 00:25:20,633
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

448
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:22,500
I've already asked Kiko
to let us know

449
00:25:22,633 --> 00:25:24,533
when he figures out the clue
in the book.

450
00:25:24,667 --> 00:25:26,667
Alright, be careful.

451
00:25:27,433 --> 00:25:28,767
- You guys too.
- Bye, Luna.

452
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,867
<i>I will help you look
for the treasure.</i>

453
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:42,867
<i> Shh.</i>

454
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:45,767
<i>It seems like someone
is following us.</i>

455
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:46,833
<i> Huh?</i>

456
00:25:48,867 --> 00:25:50,733
<i>Almazan's trial is
about to begin.</i>

457
00:25:50,867 --> 00:25:52,200
<i>He was transferred
to the city jail.</i>

458
00:25:53,233 --> 00:25:54,000
<i> Perfect timing.</i>

459
00:25:54,133 --> 00:25:56,167
<i>Make sure he never
speaks again.</i>

460
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,200
[GUNSHOT]

461
00:25:57,333 --> 00:25:59,000
<i>- Thieves!
- Luna!</i>

462
00:25:59,133 --> 00:26:00,033
<i> Hurry up!</i>

463
00:26:01,567 --> 00:26:03,133
<i>- Gio!
- Luna!</i>
